The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, May 12: The Bank of Rajasthan will issue one bonus share for every four equity shares held by the existing shareholders. The board of directors also declared a dividend of 20 per cent for 2006-07. The bank is yet to declare its results for the quarter ended March 31, 2007. 

 Mumbai, May 12: Indias forex reserves decreased by $26 million to $204.009 billion during the week ended May 4, from $204.135 billion in the seven-day period ended April 27. 

 New Delhi, May 12: The Planning Commission is in favour of waiving farm loans on a selective basis, restructuring subsidies and increasing investments in rural infrastructure to push the farm growth rate to 4 per cent during the 11th plan.

 Calcutta, May 12: Uganda has sought investment from India and urged for more liberal trade ties between the two countries.




